# Millennium CRM — Project Context

## Owner & Purpose
- Non-developer owner acquired auto insurance agency in Clarksville, TN
- ~800 active policies; ~50% Spanish-speaking clients
- Replacing AgencyZoom; carriers include Trexis, Progressive, GAINSCO, Foremost, Safeco, National General, Bristol West, Geico

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS (dark navy `#0f1117`, blue accents)
- Supabase: `policies`, `contact_log`, `automations` tables
- Hosted on Vercel: https://millennium-crm.vercel.app
- GitHub: https://github.com/tagxoxo/millennium-crm (private)

## Env Vars (`.env.local` / Vercel)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`, `SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY`
- `CRM_PASSWORD` — site login password (middleware + `/login`)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_REVIEW_LINK` — for post-retention automation template

## Architecture Notes
- Server reads: `getSupabaseServer()` in `lib/supabase/server.ts` (secret key, `cache: no-store`)
- Browser writes for policies: **use `/api/policies/[id]` PATCH** — do NOT save via browser Supabase client (hangs on Vercel)
- CSV import: **use `/api/import` POST** — batch insert on server, not browser one-by-one
- Password auth: `middleware.ts` + `lib/auth.ts` + `/api/auth`
- Route group `(crm)/` has sidebar layout; `/login` has no sidebar
- `fetchAllPolicies()` in `lib/policies.ts` paginates for large books

## Pages Built
1. **Dashboard** — KPIs, kanban (5 stages), urgent renewals (30 days)
2. **Policies** — searchable table, carrier/stage/language filters
3. **Policy Detail** — info card, Edit Client Info, stage dropdown, contact timeline, log contact
4. **Import** — AdaptAI CSV upload, column mapping, import summary
5. **Automations** — toggle cards + create form (templates only; **no auto-send engine yet**)

## Carriers (DB + UI)
`trexis`, `progressive`, `gainsco`, `foremost`, `safeco`, `national_general`, `bristol_west`, `geico`, `liberty_mutual_bop`, `liberty_mutual_surety_bond`, `tapco`, `cna`, `bruce_messier`, `mesa`, `acceptance_independent`
- SQL migration: `supabase/add-carriers.sql` if constraint errors on save

## Not Built Yet
- Email/SMS/WhatsApp sending (needs Resend/Twilio + Vercel Cron)
- Automations are config-only; toggles ON ≠ messages sent
- Per-user accounts (single shared `CRM_PASSWORD` only)

## Dev & Deploy Commands
```bash
npm run dev          # local dev
npm run dev:clean    # rm -rf .next && dev (fixes stale cache / missing CSS)
vercel --prod --yes  # deploy from CLI (logged in as tagxoxo)
bash setup-vercel-env.sh  # sync .env.local → Vercel env vars
```

## Git & GitHub (end of every session)
- Remote: https://github.com/tagxoxo/millennium-crm (private), branch `main`
- **Always commit and push to GitHub before ending a session** if there are any code changes
- Never commit `.env.local` or secrets; use `.env.example` for templates only
- GitHub CLI is logged in as `tagxoxo` — use `gh auth setup-git` if `git push` fails
- Commit message: short summary of why; push with `git push origin main`

## Common Issues
- **"Cannot find module ./995.js"** or white unstyled page → run `npm run dev:clean`
- **Stale dashboard data after import** → fixed with `revalidate = 0` + no-store fetch
- **ByteString / char 8232 error on Vercel** → invisible chars in env vars; re-type in Vercel dashboard
- **Save stuck on "Saving..."** → fixed via server API route, not browser Supabase
- Port 3000 busy → use 3001 or kill old `next dev` processes

## Code Conventions
- Clean, simple code; explain steps to non-developer owner
- Go step-by-step; pause after major pages for confirmation
- Never commit `.env.local`; use `.env.example` as template
- Commission estimate: 12% annual in `lib/dashboard.ts` (`COMMISSION_RATE`)

## User Preferences
- Plain English explanations for terminal commands
- Paste exact errors with click-by-click fixes
- Do not over-engineer; minimize scope per task
